    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="1286"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1286">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_JCS1">J. C. S.</gloss> Files</note>
                <head>No. 1286<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the United States Chiefs of Staff</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C. C. S.</gloss> 889/3</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-21">21 July
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">British Participation in the <gloss target="#t_War1"
                            >War</gloss> Against Japan</hi>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_MGAD1">General MacArthur</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_NFACW1">Admiral Nimitz</persName> welcome the visit of a British
                    corps commander and accompanying officers. <persName corresp="#p_MGAD1">General
                        MacArthur</persName> suggests that they should arrive at an early date, and
                    if practicable by 1 August.</p>
                <p>It is suggested that further matters connected with this visit be handled on an
                    operational basis between the British Joint Staff Mission and the operating
                    agencies concerned of the <gloss target="#t_War1">War</gloss> and Navy
                    Departments</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
